{
  "text": "The top is NR5A2. NR5A2, a member of a nuclear receptor subfamily, is a liver recepter homolog1 (LRH-1). Fayard et al [CITATION_1] showed that LRH-1 is abundantly expressed in pancreas. Furthermore, their in situ hybridization and gene expression studies demonstrated that both LRH and carboxyl ester lipase (CEL) are co-expressed and confi ned to the exocrine pancreas.",
